    <div class="history"> 
        <div> 
            <h1>Hector Pieterson Memorial </h1>
        </div>

        <div class="hector">
        The Hector Pieterson Memorial and Museum honors the role of South African students in the struggle against
        apartheid, particularly the role of school children who participated in the 1976 Soweto protests, many of whom
        were shot by apartheid police while protesting against the poor quality of education in black schools.
        
        <img src="PICS/memorial.jpg" width="100">
    </div>
         
    
    
        
       

     
         

         
        <h1>Wits Art Museum</h1>
        <div class="art">
        Leading African art museum. 11 000 African artworks, traditional, modern, and contemporary, from the 19th
        century to the present. Temporary exhibitions and educational programs are very busy. In a bustling
        neighborhood, award-winning contemporary architecture.
        <img src="PICS/was.jpg" width="100">
    </div>

        <h1>Freedom Park Heritage Site & Museum</h1>
        <div class="freedom">
        South Africa commemorates those who gave their lives in the struggle for a free and democratic South Africa at
        Freedom Park. It is dotted with memorials and beautiful gardens dedicated to the heroes of South Africa's past
        conflicts.
        <img src="PICS/freedom.jpg" width="100">

